    "raw_text": "Student Essay Contest to Celebrate America250, Diamond Says\nMay 8, 2026\nJONESTOWN – A newly created student essay contest invites Pennsylvania high school students to participate in a historic statewide initiative commemorating the 250th anniversary of the United States, according to Rep. Russ Diamond (R-Lebanon).\nA component of the America250 celebrations includes a ceremonial session of the Pennsylvania House of Representatives on Wednesday, Sept. 9, at Congress Hall in Philadelphia. Each House district will select one student to represent their community and take part in the event, which aims to highlight the legislative branch’s role and encourage youth participation in government.\n“This anniversary offers a valuable moment for students to consider our nation’s founding ideals and how they continue to shape our lives today,” Diamond said. “I encourage students to take part, share their viewpoints, and engage in this meaningful civic opportunity.”\nRising high school juniors or seniors who reside in the 102nd District are eligible to enter by submitting an essay about the country’s founding principles. The deadline to apply is June 1.\nEducators and school administrators are encouraged to share the contest with eligible students and support their participation.\nMunicipalities in the 102nd District include Annville, Bethel, East Hanover, Heidelberg, Jackson, Millcreek, North Annville, North Londonderry, Swatara and Union townships as well as Cleona, Jonestown, Myerstown, Palmyra and Richland boroughs.\nSubmit essays by emailing rmiccarelli@pahousegop.com. Call 717-277-2101 with questions.\nRepresentative Russ Diamond\n102nd  District\nPennsylvania House of Representatives\nMedia Contact: Jennifer Fitch\n717.260.6563\njfitch@pahousegop.com\nRepDiamond.com\nShare\nSign Up to Receive Legislative Email Updates\nKeep up-to-date on the latest legislative and community news. Your email address will be used strictly for legislative purposes.\nEmail*\nZIP Code\nSubscribe",
    "ai_summary": {
      "summary": "Rep. Russ Diamond is announcing a student essay contest for rising high school juniors and seniors in Pennsylvania's 102nd District. The winner will represent their district at a ceremonial session of the Pennsylvania House of Representatives on September 9, 2026, at Congress Hall in Philadelphia, as part of the U.S. 250th anniversary celebrations. Essays are due by June 1 and should address the country's founding principles.",
